1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,525
Stop scrolling.

2
00:00:01,525 --> 00:00:09,662
I just spent hours analyzing how $100 million startups handle viral content, and their secret sauce is shockingly simple.

3
00:00:09,662 --> 00:00:13,050
First, stop creating new things constantly.

4
00:00:13,050 --> 00:00:20,250
Use the one-to-N principle: one core idea becomes five pieces of content—a thread, a TikTok, a Short.

5
00:00:20,250 --> 00:00:23,612
The effort is in the thinking, not the reformatting.

6
00:00:23,612 --> 00:00:27,012
Second, viral hooks are actually a science.

7
00:00:27,012 --> 00:00:34,062
They fall into five categories: controversy, curiosity, shock, story, or a simple list.

8
00:00:34,062 --> 00:00:37,937
You don't guess, you test which one works for your audience.

9
00:00:37,937 --> 00:00:41,700
Third, the creators winning right now have pipelines.

10
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:47,012
They score their hooks, automate the boring parts, and build systems based on data.

11
00:00:47,012 --> 00:00:49,925
It's about working smarter, not harder.

12
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:51,662
The game has changed.

13
00:00:51,662 --> 00:00:53,512
Are you ready to adapt?

